race.comment: Onto our feature of the day, the Orr Stakes. Not a huge field, but two very good horses dominate the market headed by JIMMYSSTAR (1). He was ridden more positively in The Everest two back and was game in defeat behind Ka Ying Rising, atoning with a big win in wet conditions last time over 1300m, coming right away there. If anything, he's even better suited at 1400m and on his bulk of work, he deserves to be favourite. ANGEL CAPITAL (5) is a huge threat. He should've won the Rupert Clarke here two back in an absolute horror show. Coming back to a moderately run Everest at 1200m was against him, but his last 100m and through the line was enormous, climbing all over them, only 0.6 lengths off Jimmy. Fresher legs here and clear air out wide could be the difference. EVAPORATE (2) is flying, he was huge in the Toorak and very game in the Golden Eagle. He'll be in front of the dangers and tough to get past. VINROCK (7) and BOSUSTOW (3) can battle for the other first four spot.
